Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that vertices covered by matching M are also covered by the symmetric difference M ∆ E(P).

The key insight is that for an augmenting path P, the vertices in V(G, M) that are on the path P remain covered (by edges from the symmetric difference), and vertices in V(G, M) not on the path are covered by edges in M that remain in M ∆ E(P).

```lean
lemma IsAugPath.augment_vertex_subset (h : G.IsAugPath hM P) : V(G, M) ⊆ V(G, M ∆ E(P)) := by
  intro v hv
  obtain ⟨e, heM, hve⟩ := hv
  by_cases heP : e ∈ E(P)
  · -- e is in the path, so v is an internal vertex of P
    -- Since v ≠ P.first and v ≠ P.last (as those are not in V(G,M))
    -- v must be incident to another edge of P
    have hvfirst : v ≠ P.first := fun hvf ↦ h.first_not_in (hvf ▸ hv)
    have hvlast : v ≠ P.last := fun hvl ↦ h.last_not_in (hvl ▸ hv)
    obtain ⟨f, hfP, hfv, hef⟩ := h.toIsPath.isTrail.exists_ne_edge_of_mem_vertex heP hve hvfirst hvlast
    have hfM : f ∉ M := by
      intro hfM
      exact hM.disjoint heM hfM hef |>.notMem_of_mem_left hve hfv
    exact ⟨f, Or.inr ⟨hfP, hfM⟩, hfv⟩
  · exact ⟨e, Or.inl ⟨heM, heP⟩, hve⟩
```
